Description: Miniature Greek style trade amphora pronounced shoulder; two handles attached to neck.
Curator's comments: This is a model of an Greek transport amphora; compare for example the model amphora GR 1888,0208.165 from Tell Dafana. The fact it is a complete model of an amphora from the 1886 season means this is most likely from the cemetery (Gardner 1888, 28).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IA.50)
